@notice Logic for transferring the tokens and calling the recipient. It's on the receiver to
         make sure the call doesn't revert, otherwise the tokens won't be transferred.
         The _transfer function is not used because we want to be able to embed the native token
         into the cfReceive call to avoid doing two external calls.
         In case of revertion the tokens will remain in the Vault. Therefore, the destination
         contract must ensure it doesn't revert e.g. using try-catch mechanisms.

xCallNative(uint32,string,string,bytes,u.notice: Performs a cross-chain call to the destination address on the destination chain. Native tokens must be paid          to this contract. The swap intent determines if the provided tokens should be swapped to a different token          and transferred as part of the cross-chain call. Otherwise, all tokens are used as a payment for gas on the destination chain.          The message parameter is transmitted to the destination chain as part of the cross-chain call.

params.dstAddress: String containing the destination address on the destination chain.
params.dstChain: The destination chain according to the Chainflip Protocol's nomenclature.
params.dstNativeGas: The amount of native gas to be used on the destination chain's call.
params.message: The message to be sent to the egress chain. This is a general purpose message.
params.refundAddress: Address to refund any excess gas left from the execution of the xCall on the dstChain. This address                      is in the context of the srcChain.
params.swapIntent: String containing the specifics of the swap to be performed, if any, as part of the xCall. The string                      must follow Chainflip's nomenclature. An empty swapIntent implies that no swap needs to take place                      and the source token will be used for gas in a swapless xCall.

xCallToken(uint32,string,string,bytes,ui.details: Checking the validity of inputs shall be done as part of the event witnessing. Only the amount is checked          to explicity indicate that an amount is required.
xCallToken(uint32,string,string,bytes,ui.notice: Performs a cross-chain call to the destination chain and destination address. An ERC20 token amount          needs to be approved to this contract. The ERC20 token must be supported by the Chainflip Protocol.          The swap intent determines whether the provided tokens should be swapped to a different token          by the Chainflip Protocol. If so, the swapped tokens will be transferred to the destination chain as part          of the cross-chain call. Otherwise, the tokens are used as a payment for gas on the destination chain.          The message parameter is transmitted to the destination chain as part of the cross-chain call.

params.dstAddress: String containing the destination address on the destination chain.
params.dstChain: The destination chain according to the Chainflip Protocol's nomenclature.
params.dstNativeGas: The amount of native gas to be used on the destination chain's call. That gas will be paid with the                      source token.
params.message: The message to be sent to the egress chain. This is a general purpose message.
params.refundAddress: Address to refund any excess gas left from the execution of the xCall on the dstChain. This address                      is in the context of the srcChain.
params.swapIntent: String containing the specifics of the swap to be performed as part of the xCall. An empty swapIntent                       implies that no swap needs to take place and the source token will be used for gas in a swapless xCall.

params.dstChain: The destination chain according to the Chainflip Protocol's nomenclature.
params.swapIntent: String containing the specifics of the swap to be performed according to Chainflip's nomenclature.

params.srcToken: Address of the source token to swap.
params.swapIntent: String containing the specifics of the swap to be performed according to Chainflip's nomenclature.
